name: 3,4-dimethyl-cis-2-pentene
source: American Petroleum Institute. Research Project 44; Selected Values of Properties of Hydrocarbons and Related Compounds. Texas A & M University; College Station; TX; 1973.
Reason: 3,4-dimethyl-cis-2-pentene has a melting point of -109.4°C. The basic unit for comparison is cis-2-pentene, which has a melting point of -109.4°C. The methyl groups increase the melting point due to the increase in molecular weight and rigidity of the structure. Each methyl group may add approximately +10 due to the increase in molecular weight and rigidity of the structure.
